40|$|Since 1999 an {{increase}} in magnitude and volatility of the <b>credit</b> <b>spread</b> is observable in the German bond market. This paper analyses the <b>credit</b> <b>spread</b> of German industrial bonds focussing {{on the one hand}} on the recent period of high volatility of the <b>credit</b> <b>spread</b> {{and on the other hand}} on possible influences of structural demand and supply effects. Our empirical estimation is conducted using an Error Correction Model (ECM) for a dataset of monthly time series from 1970 to 2003. We provide evidence on a significant impact of supply effects on the <b>credit</b> <b>spread.</b> Our in-sample forecasts trace the volatility of the <b>credit</b> <b>spread</b> surprisingly well...|$|R
